News - Date: 25 February 2018 Written by: Anton van Zyl / Viewed: 315 The national budget had been tabled and we're still trying to make sense of the figures. A group of really clever programme developers decided to make life easier for the rest of us and built a little tool that tells us just how much of our worktime is spent on working for SARS. It's kinda depressing, but still interesting. All you need to do is to put your annual salary in the block and the tool will tell you how much more you will have to work to keep the taxman satisfied. (Well, at least for the next year)  Tax Clock  Anton van Zyl has been with the Zoutpansberger and Limpopo Mirror for over 27 years. He graduated at the the Rand Afrikaans University (now University of Johannesburg) and obtained a BA Communications degree. He is a founder member of the Association of Independent Publishers.  Email: anton@zoutnet.co.za